  "_comment": "Coarse ocean-basin tiling for routing normalized features into per-region FlatGeobuf extracts. A feature is assigned by testing its bbox-centroid against these polygons in array order; first containing polygon wins (ties broken by order). Regions deliberately overlap at edges; order resolves the overlap. Slugs match the plugin config region enum. sw-pacific is authored as two polygons so it is antimeridian-safe: Fiji (lon ~+179 and ~-179) lands in sw-pacific from either side. Bboxes are coarse coastal-cruising envelopes, not legal boundaries.",
